Class
Description
Administrator
Represents an administrator in the hospital management system.
AdministratorController
The AdministratorController class provides methods for managing and controlling administrative tasks in the system, such as adding/removing staff, approving replenishments, managing stock levels, and viewing appointment records.
AdministratorView
The AdministratorView class provides the user interface for the administrator to interact with the hospital management system.
Appointment
Represents an appointment in the hospital management system.
Appointment.AppointmentStatus
Enum representing the various statuses of an appointment.
Appointment.PrescribedMedication
Represents a medication prescribed during an appointment.
AppointmentController
The AppointmentController class provides methods to manage and modify appointments, including adding, updating, retrieving appointment details, and processing prescribed medications.
AppointmentReader
The AppointmentReader class implements the DataReader interface to read and load Appointment data from a CSV file into the system's data storage.
AppointmentRecords
The `AppointmentRecords` class manages the list of appointments and provides various methods to retrieve, modify, and manage appointments, such as getting available slots, retrieving appointments by status, and adding or removing appointments.
AppointmentWriter
AppointmentWriter class is used to write appointment attributes to a CSV file.
Authenticator
The `Authenticator` class provides methods to authenticate users based on their user ID and password.
ControllerInterface
The ControllerInterface defines a contract for controllers that manage user-related actions.
DataPrinter
The DataPrinter interface provides a contract for classes to implement data writing functionality.
DataReader
Interface DataReader provides a contract for classes that implement this interface.
DataStorage
The `DataStorage` class handles the loading and saving of records for various entities such as medicine, staff, patients, appointments, and replenishments.
DataWriter<T>
The DataWriter interface provides a contract for classes that handle writing data to CSV files to provide persistent storage.
Doctor
Represents a doctor in the hospital management system.
DoctorController
The DoctorController class manages the operations of a doctor within the healthcare system.
DoctorView
The `DoctorView` class represents the interface for doctors to interact with the hospital management system.
HospitalManagementSystem
The main class for the Hospital Management System.
Inventory
The `Inventory` class represents a collection of medicines and provides methods to manage the inventory, such as adding and removing medicines, viewing the inventory, and retrieving specific medicines by name.
Medicine
Represents a medicine in the hospital management system.
MedicineController
The MedicineController class is responsible for managing the operations related to medicines in the inventory.
MedicineReader
The MedicineReader class implements the DataReader interface to read and load medicine data from a CSV file into the system's data storage.
MedicineWriter
MedicineWriter class is used to write Medicine attributes to a CSV file.
Password
The `Password` class represents a hashed password using the SHA-256 algorithm.
Patient
Represents a patient in the hospital management system.
PatientController
The PatientController class handles the operations for managing patient-related actions, such as retrieving and updating patient information, scheduling, rescheduling, and canceling appointments.
PatientListReader
The PatientListReader class implements the DataReader interface to read and load medicine data from a CSV file into the system's data storage.
PatientRecords
Manages the collection of patient records within the system.
PatientView
The PatientView class provides the user interface for patient-related functionalities.
PatientWriter
PatientWriter class is used to write Patient attributes to a CSV file.
Pharmacist
Represents a pharmacist in the hospital management system.
PharmacistController
The PharmacistController class handles the operations related to a pharmacist's responsibilities.
PharmacistView
The `PharmacistView` class provides the user interface for pharmacists in the Hospital Management System.
Replenishment
Represents a replenishment request for medicine in the hospital management system.
Replenishment.Status
Enumeration for the possible statuses of a replenishment request.
ReplenishmentController
The ReplenishmentController class manages replenishment requests for the inventory.
ReplenishmentReader
ReplenishmentReader is a class responsible for reading replenishment data from a CSV file and populating it into the DataStorage object.
ReplenishmentRecords
Manages the collection of replenishment records within the system.
ReplenishmentWriter
ReplenishmentWriter class is used to write Replenishment attributes to a CSV file.
Staff
Represents an abstract staff member in the hospital management system.
StaffController
The StaffController class manages staff records, allowing for staff additions, updates, and removals.
StaffListReader
StaffListReader is a class responsible for reading staff data from a CSV file and populating it into the DataStorage object.
StaffRecords
Manages the collection of staff records within the system.
StaffWriter
StaffWriter is a class responsible for writing staff data to a CSV file.
User
Represents a generic user in the hospital management system.
UserController
The UserController class manages user authentication and user session management in the system.
UserView
The `UserView` class handles the user interface for the Hospital Management System.
ViewInterface
